Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  
AS TO COUNT 1-
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction consecutive to any other sentence; release ONLY for inmate work assignments and The Day Reporting Center; with credit for 26 days time served. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring. 
COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed defendant on probation for 2 YEARS.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION
- Maintain Absolute Sobriety: No use or possession/use of alcohol or controlled substances without a valid prescription for defendant or defendants child,  taken in the manner and fashion as prescribed.
- Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.  
- Must complete UCC program 
- Department of Corrections must conduct drug and alcohol testing at least 1 time per month for the first year of probation.
- Defendant to notify Department of Corrections agent of all prescriptions within 3 business days of receiving prescription from medical professional.
- Fill all prescriptions at one pharmacy, unless otherwise approved by Department of Corrections Agent, and notify the Department of Corrections agent of the pharmacy used. 
 - No possession of any drug paraphernalia for personal use, manufacturing, delivering or for distribution.
- No possession of any firearms or weapons, firearm ammunition, firearm magazine, firearm holster, or any body armor.
- Engage in fulltime employment, school or AODA treatment or any combination. 
- No contact with Matthew M. (DOB 08-24-1991), when he is in possession of controlled substance without a valid prescription or when he is using a controlled substance without a valid prescription.
- If any, defendant must comply with all childrens court and BCW orders.
- Court ordered Defendant to comply with all child support court orders.
- Complete Parenting or if UCC has a parenting component. 
- Fine is set at ZERO.
- Provide DNA sample, if not already done. 
- Court ordered defendant to serve 45 DAYS CONDITION TIME  in the House of Correction without goodtime credit; release ONLY for UCC AODA program and inmate work assignments. Court notes a strong objection to electronic monitoring.  This is stayed to use as follows: 
* First violation of positive drug or alcohol test, OR if does not complete UCC program to serve 10 days.
*Second violation of positive drug or alcohol test, OR if does not complete UCC program to serve 15 days.
*Third violation of positive drug or alcohol test, OR if does not complete UCC program to serve 20 days.
